        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:47PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Round Oak, or 9 miles
northwest of Gray, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Round Oak, Monticello, Stanfordville, Adgateville, and Hillsboro.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
